
$ fdisk /dev/xvdf

(Use options N to create a new partition and all the defaults for creating 1 full partition for entire volume and option W to write the partition in the filesystem)

NAME    MAJ:MIN RM  SIZE RO TYPE MOUNTPOINT
xvda    202:0    0    8G  0 disk 
??xvda1 202:1    0    8G  0 part /
xvdf    202:80   0  20G  0 disk 
??xvdf1 202:81   0  20G  0 part


$ mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdf1

$ ls -Zd /var
drwxr-xr-x. root root system_u:object_r:var_t:s0  /var
* Note the context type “var_t”

Mount the formated partition on /mnt
$ mount /dev/xvdf1 /mnt

Copy over data from /var to /mnt
$ sudo shopt -s dotglob
$ sudo rsync -aulvXpogtr /var/* /mnt

Confirmed the SELinux context on /mnt
$ ls -Zd /mnt
drwxr-xr-x. root root system_u:object_r:file_t:s0 mnt
* Note the context type “file_t”

Change context type on /mnt to match /var
$ sudo chcon -t var_t /mnt

Check context on /mnt 
ls -Zd /mnt
drwxr-xr-x. root root system_u:object_r:var_t:s0 /mnt

Umount from /mnt
$ umount /mnt

Make the entry in fstab as below:
/dev/xvdf1   /var       ext4    defaults,noatime,nofail 0   2

Change the /var to a new location and create another /var directory and mount the new volume:
$ sudo mv /var/ /var.old
$ sudo mkdir /var

This time use the mount -a in verbose mode as below:
$ sudo mount -av 

Reboot and Check!
